fields.description: Additional details about the health check or the recommended action. For exmaple, the string value can be download.microsoft.com:443;software-download.microsoft.com:443; Read-only.
fields.name: AdditionalDetail

fields.description: The unique identifier of the health check item-related activities. This identifier can be useful in troubleshooting.
fields.name: CorrelationId

fields.description: The display name for this health check item.
fields.name: DisplayName

fields.description: The value cannot be modified and is automatically populated when the health check ends. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2024 would look like this: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z'. Returned by default. Read-only.
fields.name: EndDateTime

fields.description: The type of error that occurred during this health check. Possible values are: endpointConnectivityCheckCloudPcUrlNotAllowListed, endpointConnectivityCheckWVDUrlNotAllowListed, etc. (The all possible values can refer to cloudPcOnPremisesConnectionHealthCheckErrorType) Read-Only.
fields.name: ErrorType

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: The recommended action to fix the corresponding error. For example, The Active Directory domain join check failed because the password of the domain join user has expired. Read-Only.
fields.name: RecommendedAction

fields.description: The value cannot be modified and is automatically populated when the health check starts. The Timestamp type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is in  Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2024 would look like this: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z'. Returned by default. Read-only.
fields.name: StartDateTime
